==English==
''Alternative spelling '''syphon'''''

===Etymology===
From Greek ''σίφων'' a pipe or tube.

===Noun===
'''siphon'''
# a bent pipe or tube with one end lower than the other, used to move liquid from [[reservoir]] to another.
# a [[soda siphon]]
# {{biology}} a tubelike organ found in animals or elongated cell found in plants.

===Verb===
# to use a siphon for moving a liquid.
#: ''He used a rubber tube to siphon [[petrol]] from the [[car]]'s fuel tank.''
